From: Fennec Authors <patches@fennec.computer>
Date: Mon, 08 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ui: uBlock Origin blocked-requests toolbar indicator

Adds a compact status indicator to the Fennec toolbar (the BrowserAction
button area, left of the address bar) that shows the number of requests
blocked by uBlock Origin for the current tab.

Display behaviour:
  - Hidden when no requests have been blocked on the current page (0).
  - Shows the integer count "12", "247", "1.3k", etc. in a pill badge
    positioned at the bottom-right of the uBO toolbar button icon.
  - Badge colour:
      0 blocked  → no badge
      1–9        → --fnc-color-fox-400 (neutral)
      10–99      → #f59e0b (amber)
      100+       → #ef4444 (red)
  - Resets to 0 on every navigation commit in the active tab.
  - Updates live as uBO fires block events for the current tab.

Implementation:
  - FennecUBlockBadge class subscribes to webRequest.onBeforeRequest
    events filtered to the active tab and increments a per-tab counter.
  - Counter is stored in a std::unordered_map<int, int> keyed by tab_id,
    reset by WebContentsObserver::DidFinishNavigation.
  - Badge rendering uses the existing BrowserAction badge API
    (chrome.browserAction.setBadgeText / setBadgeBackgroundColor).

PILLAR: Calm UI — indicator is present but unobtrusive; hidden at zero.
JOURNAL: none (badge state is not a network request).

